.TH WEBSERVER-DEPLOYER 1
.SH NAME
.B webserver-deployer 
\- Manage and deploy webservers

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B webserver-deployer 
help
\- Show cmd list

.B webserver-deployer 
create 
\- Create a config file by asking the user

.B webserver-deployer 
deploy \fIfile\fR [\fIfile\fR ...] 
\- Deploy new VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
start \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR ...] 
\- Start VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
stop \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR ...] 
\- Halt VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
update
\- Update installed VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
list
\- List installed VMs

.B sudo 
env "PATH=$PATH" "HOME=$HOME" .B 
.B webserver-deployer 
update-hosts
\- Update /etc/hosts (as root)

.B webserver-deployer 
remove \fIname\fR [\fIname\fR ...] 
\- Delete VMs

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B webserver-deployer
\-
Manage and deploy webservers

.B webserver-deployer 
help
\- Show cmd list

.B webserver-deployer 
create 
\- Create a config file by asking the user

.B webserver-deployer 
deploy
\- Deploy new VMs and install + configure packages

.B webserver-deployer 
start 
\- Start VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
stop 
\- Halt VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
update
\- Update installed VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
list
\- List installed VMs

.B webserver-deployer 
update-hosts
\- Update /etc/hosts (as root)

.B webserver-deployer 
remove 
\- Delete VMs

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.\fIfile\fR The config file to read
.\fIname\fR Name of the machine to edit